<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="349" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="349">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,799,825]" pageId="18" pageNumber="349">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet of the new species is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1073,1177,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="349">lunulatus</emphasis>
, referring to the dorsal lobe of the sacculus dilated in lunulate shape distally.
</paragraph>
